  "body": "As the title says, firing a transaction immediately with data received from `scanQRCode` causes the transaction modal to disappear. I believe it has something to do with the browser only expecting one overlay modal. Since the QR scan modal takes precedence, if there is not sufficient time for the QR scan modal to disappear _before_ the transaction modal appears, then the transaction modal will slide to the bottom and hide behind the browser.\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to be able to scan a QR code where the data from the QR code is used to fire a transaction so that I can interact with a dapp.\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want to be able to use QR functionality without the `setTimeout` seen below:\r\n```\r\nwindow.web3.currentProvider\r\n  .scanQRCode()\r\n  .then(data => {\r\n    setTimeout(() => {\r\n      Contract.method(data)\r\n        .send({ ... })\r\n        ...\r\n    }, 1000)\r\n  })\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n*Summary*: I built a dapp that scans a QR code and uses the data to call a transaction immediately. Doing so would cause the transaction modal in the browser to disappear. The solution was to add a `setTimeout` to create some time between the QR scan modal and the trasnsaction modal.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThe hope is that the modals can overlay each other or both exist at the same time.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nIf a transaction is immediatly called from data gained from a QR code scan, while the QR scan modal is moving off the screen, the transaction modal will appear and then disappear quickly. No more transactions can be called.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nWrite a dapp that takes data from a QR code and calls a transaction from that data. Using it in the context of the status browser, the transaction modal will disappear soon after appearing.\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go to said dapp\r\n- Scan QR code\r\n- Watch the transaction modal appear and disappear\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nI assume that enabling the existence of multiple modals would be the solution.\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n- [ ] Allow modals to exist simutaneously\r\n- [ ] Make tx modal take precednce over qr screen\r\n- [ ] If QR screen is not the forward-most screen, disable camera\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.30\r\n* Operating System: iOS",
